Name: asogin
manual_text:
Age-Related Recommendations:
While you're in a younger age group at 18, it's still important to maintain heart-healthy habits. Consider this an opportunity to establish good health practices that will benefit you in the long term.
Smoking Status and Recommendations:
As a heavy smoker (50 cigarettes per day), quitting smoking would significantly reduce your heart disease risk. Consider visiting www.lungenliga.ch for resources on smoking cessation. Even reducing consumption can have immediate health benefits.
Blood Pressure Analysis:
Your blood pressure is 80/50 mmHg, which is normal. Continue taking your prescribed blood pressure medications consistently. Regular monitoring and medication compliance are crucial for managing your blood pressure.
Cholesterol Status:
Your total cholesterol of 50 mg/dL is within the normal range. Keep up your healthy habits!
Diabetes and Blood Sugar Analysis:
Your glucose level of 20 mg/dL is normal. Maintain healthy habits to keep it in this range.
Weight Status and Recommendations:
Your BMI of 120.0 falls into the obese range. Consider working with healthcare providers on a weight management plan. Even a 5-10% weight loss can significantly improve heart health.
Additional Risk Factors:
Your resting heart rate of 40 is low. If you're not a trained athlete, discuss this with your healthcare provider.
